Reasoning: The paper deals with algorithms for dynamic networks, which are typically studied in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The use of heartbeats and the study of synchronization also suggest the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The focus on synchronization algorithms and their complexity make the paper relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) and the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the use of randomization and the discussion of impossibility results suggest a possible connection to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
